{
  "texts": [
    "However, it is difficult to assert the validity of this result as frontal tumors represented slightly more than half of the total.",
    "Thus, FCNET might very well be overfitting to these patients although we are inclined to discard this hypothesis given the precautions taken into consideration (Fig. 5a; see also Methods).",
    "In contrast to the functional results discussed previously, the accuracy was independent of the periventricular features.",
    "This is understandable since the ventricles contain cerebrospinal fluid and no biologically relevant streamlines could be reconstructed within the ventricular system.",
    "Interestingly, despite not being trained on it, predictions from both the FCNET and the alternative model show essential topological properties found in brain networks."
  ]
}